SIMPLE: incredulous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incredulous
<hw>In*cred"u*lous</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incredulus</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Credulous</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not credulous; indisposed to admit or accept that
which is related as true, skeptical; unbelieving.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A fantastical <qex>incredulous</qex> fool.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Wilkins.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Indicating, or caused by, disbelief or
incredulity.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>incredulous</xex> smile.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Longfellow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Incredible; not easy to be believed.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incredulously</ent>⟦br⟧
